      "content": "- **Core scaffold:** a **fused polycyclic aromatic system** consistent with a **phenazine/phenanthridine-like tricyclic** (extended, rigid, planar aromatics).\n- **Aryl substituent:** a **phenyl ring bearing a phenol** (`Oc1ccccc1\u2013`).\n- **Heteroatoms / functional groups:**\n  - **Phenol (Ar\u2013OH):** 1 H-bond donor / acceptor (acceptor weak when phenolic).\n  - **Two ring nitrogens as an aniline-like/diarylamine motif**: `C1N...N1` indicates **two secondary amine-type nitrogens** embedded in an aromatic/fused system.\n- **Basicity alert check:**\n  - These N atoms are **anilide/aniline-like within a highly conjugated fused aromatic system**, so their lone pairs are **delocalized** \u2192 **reduced basicity** vs typical CYP2D6 inhibitors (tertiary aliphatic amines).\n- **Physicochemical expectation (qualitative):**\n  - **High aromaticity / lipophilicity** and **planarity** (favors binding in P450 active sites in general).\n  - Likely **MW in the ~250\u2013350 range** (fits the \u201ctypical\u201d inhibitor MW window).",
