      "content": "**Features that decrease CYP2D6 inhibition likelihood (key for CYP2D6 specifically)**\n- CYP2D6 inhibition is strongly associated with a **protonatable basic N** that can form an ionic interaction with **Asp301** (a hallmark interaction for many CYP2D6 ligands/inhibitors).\n- Here, the nitrogens are **embedded in an extended aromatic system** (aniline-like) \u2192 **much less protonated at pH 7.4** than a tertiary aliphatic amine.\n- Without a reliably **cationic center**, binding may be weaker and/or shift toward other CYPs (e.g., CYP1A2 often likes planar polyaromatics).",
